```json
{
  "application": "SLURM",
  "details": {
    "job_name": "py-seaborn@0.11.2",
    "account": "use300",
    "reservation": "rocky8u7_testing",
    "partition": "ind-gpu-shared",
    "nodes": 1,
    "tasks_per_node": 1,
    "cpus_per_task": 10,
    "memory": "93G",
    "gpus": 1,
    "time": "00:30:00",
    "output": "%x.o%j.%N",
    "scheduler_module": "slurm",
    "spack_version": "0.17.3",
    "spack_instance_name": "gpu",
    "spack_instance_version": "b",
    "spack_instance_dir": "/cm/shared/apps/spack/0.17.3/gpu/b",
    "spack_package": "py-seaborn@0.11.2",
    "spack_compiler": "gcc@10.2.0",
    "spack_variants": "",
    "spack_dependencies": "^py-matplotlib@3.4.3/$(spack find --format '{hash:7}' py-matplotlib@3.4.3 % ${SPACK_COMPILER})",
    "spack_spec": "py-seaborn@0.11.2 % gcc@10.2.0  ^py-matplotlib@3.4.3/$(spack find --format '{hash:7}' py-matplotlib@3.4.3 % gcc@10.2.0)",
    "system_name": "expanse",
    "local_scratch_dir": "/scratch/${USER}/job_${SLURM_JOB_ID}",
    "tmpdir": "/scratch/${USER}/job_${SLURM_JOB_ID}",
    "dependency": "afterok:${SLURM_JOB_ID}",
    "dependent_job": "py-dask@2021.6.2.sh"
  }
}
``` 
This script uses SLURM for job management, Spack for package management, and relies on the `gcc` compiler. It defines a job named "py-seaborn@0.11.2" that uses resources like 1 node, 10 CPUs per task, 93GB of memory, and 1 GPU. The script ensures that the necessary packages and dependencies are installed using Spack before executing the job. It also sets up a local scratch directory for temporary files. The script submits a dependent job named "py-dask@2021.6.2.sh" after the current job completes successfully.
